  "prompt": "WhatsApp: I really hate this WhatsApp feature. How can I disable this?",
  "response": "If you're referring to a specific WhatsApp feature that you dislike, here are some general steps to disable or manage common features:\n\n### \u2460 **Disable Read Receipts (Blue Ticks):**\n   - Open WhatsApp > **Settings** (three dots on Android or Settings on iOS) > **Account** > **Privacy**.\n   - Scroll down and turn off **Read Receipts**.  \n   *Note:* Disabling this also prevents you from seeing others' read receipts.\n\n---\n\n### \u2461 **Disable Last Seen:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Account** > **Privacy** > **Last Seen**.\n   - Choose **Nobody** to hide your \"Last Seen\" status.\n\n---\n\n### \u2462 **Mute Group Notifications:**\n   - Open the group chat > Tap the group name at the top > Select **Mute Notifications** and choose a duration (e.g., 8 hours, 1 week, or Always).\n\n---\n\n### \u2463 **Disable Auto-Download Media:**\n   - Open **Settings** > **Storage and Data** > **Media Auto-Download**.\n   - Adjust settings for **Wi-Fi**, **Mobile Data**, and **Roaming** to prevent automatic downloads.\n\n---\n\n### \u2464 **Disable Status Updates:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Account** > **Privacy** > **Status**.\n   - Adjust who can view your status updates or hide it entirely.\n\n---\n\n### \u2465 **Stop WhatsApp Calls:**\n   - Go to **Settings** > **Account** > **Privacy** > **Calls**.\n   - You can silence calls from unknown numbers or manage who can call you.\n\n---\n\n### \u2466 **Uninstall WhatsApp:**\n   If none of the above works, you can uninstall the app or switch to a different messaging platform.\n\nLet me know the specific feature you're struggling with, and I can provide more tailored guidance!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
